\pard\f0\fs28  Several taxa, including {\b V. pratensis} Dierbach ex Walther, {\i Mitt. Thür. Bot. Ges.}{\b  2}, {\i Beih.}{\b  1}: 83 (1949), non (Bentham) Bentham ex Steudel, from the upper Rhine basin, and {\b V. stolonifera} Czern., {\i Bull. Soc. Nat. Moscou}{\b  18}({\b 2}): 133 (1845), from E.C. Europe and S.W. part of U.S.S.R., differ from subsp. ({\b b}) chiefly in having glabrous stems; their status is uncertain.
