\pard\f0\fs28  {\b V. repens} Host,{\i  Fl. Austr. }{\b 1}: 35 (1827) ({\i V. procurrens} Wallr.), from W. & W.C. Europe, differs from subsp. ({\b c}) chiefly in having the stems hairy at least below and the middle cauline leaves with 5-17 leaflets; it has 2n = 56, and may perhaps be considered as a fourth subspecies.
