\pard\f0\fs28  {\b 1} is cultivated on a small scale in many parts of Europe for its rhizome which yields the drug valerian. This drug has also been obtained from{\b  V. phu} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 32 (1753), a species of uncertain origin but said to be native in N. Anatolia. It resembles {\b 1}, but differs in having mostly undivided basal leaves and terete stems; it has been recorded in various parts of Europe as an escape from cultivation, but does not appear to be fully naturalized.
